author: Miguel Reyes
text: This time last year I found myself wanting to change my career path. I told myself “I never want to work for money again, but only because I enjoy the work I do”. I modeled Lester Brown’s spirit of absolute certainty and among at least hundreds of other applicants I got the position that would change my life and begin the path to fulfilling my own destiny. It has always been my dream to become an artist, and for the last 10 years, I’ve been wanting to become an animator. I no longer have to wake up dreading the next few hours to come. Now I wake up and get ready to have fun! Now I draw animated characters for a living and the company is paying for me to go to school and get my bachelors in animation! I believe listening to this video about 3x a day for at least a week before my interviews helped get me in the right mindset to prove I am the only candidate for the Sketch Artist position. I am so blessed and lucky, but before all that, I had to believe I was worth it. I had to look at the Fatalist in the mirror and say “I am worthy of happiness, and I deserve to realize my purpose in life.” Then the man in the mirror smiled back at me. Every step thereafter has counted towards my dreams.﻿

author: Hello there Wrong
text: Some people think they have to put things on hold when you have a child, but infants, toddlers and really young children love to learn and stay busy! Do what you like and involve them they will love it! If you garden, paint, play musical instruments, cooking/baking, exercising , sewing heck they will even clean with you! Put on some music , not too loud, and have a positive attitude and dont expect too much perfection and just have fun!! If you like photography teach your child to take photos right along your side if you park them in front of the TV then that is what they will be used to and wont want to turn it off they start living in a fantasy world! Same with internet! Avoid it as much as possible!! Dont ask your child too many questions about the future especially their adult life- it creates anxiety! Put your infant right next to you in a safe area and involve them while you do things you enjoy! They will learn to be productive too as they grow! Some of my daughters best memories are of us gardening flowers and vegetables , her first shoes were tiny garden boots.﻿

text: "What sets you on fire"... I always knew what set me on fire but I was so insecure about what other people would think. I was also scared of failure. Scared that no one would pay me or what I am doing any attention. Then I realized after years of going back and forth with myself, and having my dream keep me up at night, that what other people thought didn't matter as long as I did what I wanted to do. Even though my following is relatively small on social platforms, when I go out in to the world my presence is BIG. The expressions of gratitude I got from those who were on the brink of destruction and even SUICIDE, but changed their minds and behaviors because of the encouragement i gave to them, means more than thousands of followers. THANKS FOR THIS INSPIRATION and thought provoking message.﻿

text: Well, I'll be 60 next week (don't know how THAT happened!!!), and I can tell you that nothing will change until YOU do. Now that he's older, there are so many things that fascinate me that I can't choose one to start with! I've found that the MOST important thing is to know, love and accept YOURSELF. Once you accomplish that, everything else will fall into place. It requires effort - as does everything worth doing - but it's worth it. I have a large library of books (PDFs) that can help with this. Anyone interested can contact me thru my channel. It to that take me a week or more to respond, but I will get back to you. author: Anthony Reyes
text: My wife and kids life has gotten turned upside down last year. We had found out that my wife has stage 4 brest cancer and it's spread to her lymph nodes. She has had a numerous amount of surgeries and has been fighting for her life . It has left me with our 4 children 12, 7, 2, 1 . It's very hard and things have changed so fast. I'm lost and don't know what to do . I want to be more than what I am and do more than what I'm doing but insurance is declining everything and if I work her insurance will be canceled. So I'm working under the table but that isn't good for long term retirement, social security etc... her memory is bad , neurological issues , neuropathy and that's to list few. I feel stuck and all I want is to be the best I can be for my children and for my beautiful wife to be around for her children and watch them grow , graduate, get married, have kids, and the things every mother and parent should experience. I'm lost.....so lost. She's in another state getting treatment while I'm in another working under the tale trying to make things work. Pay bills and be here for everything and everyone. We have been together since we were 16 and wanted to start a family and we did that's what our DREAM was... and to have this happen we all feel cheated. Why? I don't understand. ...? We are not bad people and we obided by everything we we're supposed to. Why? It's like I'm stuck and don't know what to do. I look at my kids and I just want them to be good people . And I'm afraid that everything that's going on is going to affect them and I feel ad they are being subjected to this and it's not their fault. I am an emotional wreck. Anyways enough of my ranting and emotional situation.﻿

author: prdi ludi
text: I came to realize who were toxic people in my life(one of them being me myself) who dragged me down when i met this guy who became my best friend even tho i never actually told him that. He was the only inspiration i ever had in my life, not my mom, siblings, famous people, in my head nobody was worthy enough, nobody that i can look up to.... for the first time in life i knew in what direction i want to go, everything that friend did on daily basis was like an eureka to me, he thought me so much about life without even realizing it. I admired him so much i wanted to be just like him. He was the real life version of my vision what kind of person i wanted to be. And one day... i got the news that he killed himself... i was so confused why, i still am. What he did that day raised so many questions about life in general, and i just got tired of living life, just stopped caring about anyone or anything. I lost everything that day... I don't hate him for that, everything he did in life had some kind of purpose. Later i learned how fucked up his childhood was that probably led to that decision, he suffered from depression and i had no clue cause that man was the definition of happiness.... At least that's what he allowed us to see. And now 3 years latter... im still sitting in this damn uncomfortable chair feeling lost, without a job, fucked up my collage education i stopped going out of the house, got chronically ill and i still don't care cause i feel unworthy just like all the years before i met this friend. Browsing my life away on the internet trying to motivate myself again... in hopes somebody or something will kindle the fire in me. I get myself moving for a few days a month, but that quickly falls apart cause i cant deal with my head and stay consistent at anything. So what i started doing is listening to these speeches as much as i can to burn it into my brain. To force myself to say yes to goals i was once 'hungry' for. Talking to people became my worst fear, cause i cant really explain my thought process without being judged so im writing this here just to get it out... have a happy and productive decade people.﻿

author: William Paterson
text: My fear friends. This is a great video full of useful info. Think of all of the inventions that have come to man's mind and then see that single thought Produced as a material product in Our world. EVERYTHING begins with a thought ! What's the worse thing mankind has ever invented ???? Is it the Nuclear Bomb that has such a destructive force that it could kill EVERY living thing on Our world? The answer is "No". You'll laugh When I tell you that one of the most DESTRUCTIVE objects in YOUR life is in nearly everyone's house and it's NOT powered by electricity. What is it? It's the MIRROR in your bedroom, bathroom, hall and wherever. When we look at our reflection, We instantly JUDGE ourselves on our appearances. The mirror tells us that We're attractive, ugly, young, old, fat, thin, and by your OWN JUDGEMENTof self, YOU either like or hate what you see. YOUR mirror, without saying a word, tells you that you ARE better looking than others but, NOT as good looking as YOUR idol. Imagine a world without mirrors. What a different world it would be if you couldn't see your OWN reflection. Without the mirror, you would NEVER see yourself and thereby, you would have NOTHING to Compare yourself with. There would be NO competition to look better than others as no one else Would ever know what they looked like either ! What's the meaning of this rant then? Simple. DON'T look into your mirror for self appraisal, Cos if you're totally HONEST with yourself, you may see self - condemnation staring back at you. YOU ARE NOT that reflection, YOU are A child of the Universe, a Spiritual Being that exits and extends beyond time and space, so, STOP JUDGING YOURSELF AND OTHERS BY THEIR OUTWARD APPEARANCES ! Some of the Most Beautiful SPIRITUAL People you have met have looked, OUTWARDLY, like the biggest bag of garbage you've ever seen, but, INWARDLY, they are full of Wisdom, Empathy and have unlimited Compassion and Unconditional love for their fellow creatures. So, look AWAY from your mirrors and be your "true" Self as you REALLY are and were always MEANT to be. Peace and love to ALL being everywhere. William 👍 ﻿

author: Charles Shauf
text: Hey Milo, I don't think I have ever replied to anyone on YouTube, but when I read your comment, I kind of felt compelled to respond. I was also on your boat. When I was 28/29 years old, I started thinking about going back to school too. I was working in commercial insurance for about 6 years after undergrad and I absolutely just hated what I did for a living. It was scary to think that heading into my 30's that I had absolutely no idea what I was doing with my life. It was scary to think of starting all over again, especially when my friends around me were getting married/having kids/buying houses. But you know, everyone has their own roads, and everyone figures things out at their own time. Anyway, long story short, I decided to take the leap and I started working on my prerequisite courses (which took me about 2 years) before actually getting into grad school for physical therapy. I'm 35 now too and I have about a year and a half left before I graduate, and my program is a 3-4 year program at $100,000, not to mention living expenses. It's a lot of money. It's a big decision, definitely weigh out your pros and cons. I guess what I am trying to say is if you are not currently happy with what you are doing and you are certain that you want to become a dental hygienist, I figure it's worth it to be doing something that you love. I am not saying that the road is going to be easy. It has definitely been a roller coaster of emotions these last couple of years with this career change, but at the end of the day, I have absolutely no regrets. Just thought I'd share my story. Good luck to you brother!﻿

author: Shayne Williams
text: I'm not gonna lie, at first i was when i saw there was no morgan freeman, i was pissed of man. I was just a little bit in my head like "if you don't gettt shit shittt atta here." So at that point i realized, okay, obvious click bait, but then i started hearing speeches, that outright just changed my life. Motivational pieces are a dime a dozen okay, they all usually sound the same to a certain extent with slight variation, or different perspectives on already looked upon topics. But man, when that man spoke, there was something different. There was having had the hard times, there was his own self transition as well, but he made me laugh like never before. It was like combining a good black comedian, that rocky feel where you go from nothing to something but more intense, but some how still exuding this unbelievably positive outlook on life, truly vibrant energy that overwhelms you. So i just have to be the first one to say, I have got to thank you for your personal use of clickbait, because it lead me to something so powerful and life changing, that i may not have necessarily clicked with a different thumbnail. Besides, 10 times a day you click on a random clip not even looking at the title just to see some tits or some half clothes wearing woman to draw attention, i think this is using thumbnails for a good purpose for once.﻿

text: I've been watching a lot if videos about life advice and what to do and etc. It has definitely helped me, since I've been working on myself and being able to do it with a clearer mind, hell I met this girl a while back, she's gorgeous but the most important, shes a good friend, she understands me, even likes me, compliments me "you know your special right? You will find yourself Brett, but first you have to be yourself, love and care for yourself and worry about your life, cause it's so short and I just want you to be happy, don't worry about others because I will always Respect, care for you " It honestly made me want to shut down cause no one has ever said that, not no body and being who I am and what my mindset is, what she said really made me open up, like something shifted in my mind but not amazingly, but it removed some doubt and sadness, which was enough. I've been looking into film and programming. I personally also look into app development and photography, it's things I like but I never try to be me. I have my setbacks and they are my fault for allowing myself to think I'm any lower then someone. I just want to work in the creating community, I do voices. I write sometimes but mostly keeping it all in my head, which I forgot some taste ideas, but I just want to learn. author: Joani Paige
text: Realize you posted this 3 months ago but maybe you will get this. I took a course by Jose Silva through which I learned a technique to abate negative thoughts...." cancel cancel". No kidding...... when you start an internal conversation that is dark, cut yourself off and say cancel cancel. It will stop. When it starts again....cancel cancel. I added to this.......putting positive scenerios in my head when the darkness was being stubborn. Also. you can keep a written list of positive "happy"things ....your pet,a song, the trees, the feeling of jello....doesn't have to be big. just a list you can recite to yourself if the thoughts are being stubborn, look at the list and recite it , even if in your mind. I've found this extremely helpful, we're all different but it may work for you. All Best!﻿

author: Joani Paige

author: Twisted Pixie
text: Something brought me to this today. I am great full it did.. I am 56 years old, currently unemployed, and for each day that passes I find myself losing more and more of my confidence and desire of accomplishing more in my life. I know with every bit of me that there is more for me to experience and accomplish in my life, that this is not all there is, in have so much more to offer in this world. But my "Fear" seems to consume me more and more each day that passes, and that conversation going on inside has taken control each time. My daughter said to me one day " Mom, what happened to the way you use to be?" "You would never doubt yourself like you do these days". I don't have an answer for her. Hearing this today is a definite blessing, one that has allowed me to experience that empowering feeling I would get when i knew there was nothing that could stop me from achieving whatever I wanted, a feeling I have not felt in several years now. I don't know who I am today.. But I'm gonna make this my decade and find out! Thanks Les, your words are amazing, I would love to have the opportunity to see and hear you in person one day.﻿

author: Daniel Hill
text: I have a little library of motivational Youtube videos that I listen to in MP3 format. I had a bigger one, but I had to delete the ones with Gary Vaynerchuk. In my opinion, to use the F-bomb as an exclamation point to the degree he does crosses the line from motivational to crass. It's a shame, because although he has good stuff to say, the F-bombs take away from it and are unnecessary. I know he thinks he's being "real," but to me, he's being lazy and avoiding the hard work of crafting a message that gets peoples' attention by how well it's spoken, rather than get their attention through cheap shock value. Listen to Les Brown, and you'll see what I mean by "crafting a message."﻿

A list of related videos popped up, including the TedEx (have you ever watched those?) talks on "secrets to learning any language." I'm trying to learn Spanish, so I'm going to use those to help. It's not a higher-energy way of speaking, and one or two swears here or there is one thing, but over and over and over and over, creates in the listener a mindset of negativity. author: samantha mccloud
text: My goal in life is something that I have never heard of before. This idea has possibilities to benefit children in so many ways. Teaching children lessons that is one of the hardest lessons to teach child or adult. Lessons like self confidence, how to brake down goals into steps, how to do things that adults struggle with everyday. Our nation makes it impossible to understand that everyone is gifted. The only gifts that children know even exist is the most common gifts. A child with a gift or curiosity about being something that can not be explored like sports or the clubs offered within school stop exploring and feeding that gift. This is a non-profit idea that I need guidance on. I have no one in my life other than my three little girls and a family full of negative thinkers. Therefore, creating a atmosphere of loneliness, not because I do not believe in my idea or because I do not know which way to go, or because I do not believe in my self. I fear I will loose this battle if I can not find a mentor. I have asked college they said they didn't understand what I meant but good luck. Please just give me an idea on where to find a mentor. The only path I know to take is to start meaningless business until I can create this business myself. If anyone could give any tip please let me know. Thank you...﻿

author: paritosh pandey
text: Giving is living Please read this to help someone in need My brother Shantesh Ojha is an MNNIT 2012 batch passout from mechanical engineering department. He's 30 years old and got married 2 years ago. He started getting high fever from 3rd jan 2018 to 6 jan 2018 and his blood reports showed high levels of liver and kidney enzymes and on 8th jan doctors told us that he needed dialysis urgently as his kidneys had failed. We were at varanasi at that time and his condition was deteriorating rapidly so on doctors recommendation we flew him to Delhi and admitted him in Sir Ganga Ram hospital Delhi. There he was diagnosed with Acute viral Hepatitis E which resulted in his acute liver failure and acute kidney failure and they told us that it will recover by self recovery as there is no medicine for Hepatitis E but only support to the body so that it can recover by itself. There he underwent dialysis every alternate day and due to coagulopathy all in all 35 units of fresh frozen plasma and blood was transfused to him till 7th march. After that he was transferred to institute for liver and billiary sciences vasant kunj delhi for second opinion on his liver condition as even after close to 2 months time his both organs were unable to recover and his liver condition was deteriorating. Initially it had shown some recovery and major portion it was stable but it started deteriorating after 2nd march. We admitted him to ILBS on 7th march. There on 8 th march after conducting tests they told us that liver cannot recover and kidney has been lost too and he needs liver and kidney transplant as soon as possible. We inquired about best treatment for this and we consulted at other hospitals as well like max and medanta and we came to that this type of surgery has best success rate at Medanta Hospital Gurgaon. Before shifting him here we have already incurred a cost of Rs 20-22 lakhs already. And the cost for this dual transplant surgery is estimated at 35-40 lacs. This is the only option to save life of a young man filled with aspirations and dreams of future. So I request you all to please contribute whatever you can because drops make a whole ocean.🙏🏻🙏 contact number-9794837587,9140869967 The Medanta hospital which are as follows: Account name: Global Health Pvr. If u dont share the transaction receipt the contribution could not be upadated in his name. The doctors are preparing him for the dual transplant, meanwhile let us pray for his good health and take time out of our busy schedules to do our bit for the life of my brother REMEMBER TO SHARE THE SCREENSHOT OF THE RECEIPT. author: Nikhil Kalra
text: Sandeep Sir, kindly give some good time on understanding Narcissism and please deliver an insightful session on this problem w.r.t. an narcissist father, if you find it relevant & feasible. I have been facing and dealing with a narcissist father for the last 25.5 years and I don't know how to make him realize that it's not gonna work if he continues to abuse & control us emotionally. My younger brother has also started developing the same self-centered approach towards people(including his own mother) and I'm afraid that his blind faith in his "innocent & clean-hearted" dad will land him up in the worst conundrum some years down the line. My research on narcissism has convinced me to put an end to our(Dad & Mine) purely benefit-oriented relationship with my father and brother(perhaps) but my mother is the most sensitive victim cum believer of my father's sweet excuses and justification therefore I fail to implement this decision and she ends up getting abused and manipulated in an even more sweeter way and remains hooked up as he leaves no scope of doubt in his private sessions of justifying himself and winning the trust of my mother & brother again which is something that eventually maintain his fabricated public image, the only thing he is concerned. And I can assure you of the fact that this is not just me who is struggling with such non-empathetic and cruel behaviour which doesn't lets an individual to develop a sense of self-esteem and confidence of one's own real self and always seeks for approval of others because he never got validation or encouragement of how he dealt and saw the world instead was always forced to follow, agree and comply with his father's way of thinking without allowing you a moment of resistance or permission to differ with his opinion, else you get declared as a "dead investment" which becomes words of wisdom for the rest of the blind members of the family as the narcissist father ensures that he is least likely to be accused of being the real reason behind any setbacks in social life or differences between his victim and his blind followers as they are made to learn that problem lies in the abused victim and not the monster himself. Kindly give a serious thought to it. And let us know what should one practice to deal with a narcissist. Is it emotional intelligence that we should start working on or should we just leave everything and start finding the real self within OR keep on surviving with 12-hour self killing job and constantly accommodating with what people expect out of you thereafter suppressing the extended narcissistic personality within you which always gets you rejected if expressed by even 5% of it ? In case of any quick clarifications regarding narcissism, kindly search Google Images about Narcissism Personality Disorder - https://www.google.co.in/search?q=narcissistic+personality+disorder&source=lnms&tbm=isch&sa=X&ved=0ahUKEwjj_Zfg4PbYAhVGp48KHRpJCiEQ_AUICigB&biw=1536&bih=694&dpr=1.25﻿

author: Manas Mishra
text: विशाल संकलप संस्था (एन. जी. ओ) गैर सरकरी संस्था है जो कि निस्वार्थ भाव से मानवता की सेवा में पिछले दो दशकों से कार्यरत है। संस्था की नीव सन २००० में रखी गयी व २ जुलाई २००७ में संस्था रेजिस्टर कराई गयी। मानव जीवन को सफल बनाने के लिए, मुस्कान संग, मानवता की सेवा करना संस्था का मूल उद्देश्य है। प्रायः अंधेरो की बाते करने से अंधेरा दूर नहीं होता। अंधेरे की बात करने से बेहतर है कि एक छोटा सा दीप जलाय— आओ मिलकर छोटे प्रयास से, बड़े परिवर्तन की राह बनाय। ये पंक्तियां संस्था का परिचय देने के लिये पर्याप्त है। यथार्त भी यही है कि किसी भी बड़ी संख्या की गिनती इकाई से ही शुरू होती है। यदि हम सभी सुधार की शुरुआत स्वयं से करे तो कुछ भी असंभ्व नहीं। बूंद बूंद से घड़ा भरता है। उसी तरह हम एक छोटा सा दीप बनकर और अपनी स्तर की पूरी उर्जा हस्तांतरित करके, प्रकाश फैला सकते है। ये प्रकाश भी अलग ही है जो प्रकाशित करने वाले और प्रकाशित करने वाले दोनो को सुख देता है। बड़े परिवर्तन के लिए ये ज़रुरी है कि हम सब अपने अपने हिस्से की भागीदारी निभाय। तर्क देने के लिए लोग कह सकते है कि एक छोटे से दीपक से क्या होगा, सच में ज़्यदा कुछ नहीं बस इतना होगा कि रोशनी की उम्मीद छोड़ चुके शहर के जीवन में रोशनी आ जायगी और जब कभी इतिहास लिखा जायगा आपका नाम दीप जलाने वाले के रूप में लिखा जायग, अंधेरों की बात करने वालो के रूप में नहीं। विशाल संकल्प की स्थापना श्रीमति अंजली केसरी ने इन्हीं बातों को ध्यान में रखकर की। पहले संस्था का नाम नारी शक्ति जाग्रत संस्था था। लेकिन २०१६ में एक सड़क हादसे में अपने पति को खोने के बाद अंजली जी ने यह संस्था पति के स्मृतियों को चिर रखने के लिए उन्हीं को समर्पित कर दी व उनके संकल्पों को पूरा कराने का मध्यम बना दिया। वर्तमान में संस्था का नाम “ विशाल संकल्प” है। अंधेरों की बात करना नहीं बल्कि एक दीप जलाना पसंद है। उनका जो सीमित साधन होने के बावजूद मानवता की असीमित सेवा करना चाहते है। उनका जो ईश्वर के इस विज्ञान को समझते है कि जब कभी आप किसी की सेवा करते है तत्क्षण ईश्वर आपकी सेवा में किसी ना किसी को लगा देते है। उनका जो अपने देश के लिए कुछ करना चाहते है। उनका जो मानव जन्म को यूंही नहीं बिताना चाहते है। आइए हम सब मिलकर छोटे-छोटे प्रयासो से मानवता की सेवा करे। विश्वास मानिये इस दैवी कार्य से मिलने वाला सुख की तुलना आप किसी भी सुख से नहीं कर पायेंगे। https://www.facebook.com/vishalsankalp/ like and share our page﻿

author: swati lakwale
text: Kya jindagi ho gayi hai,ham khush hai ya nahi wo ham lamhe par mahsus karate hai.ham khush hai ye khud ko sabit karane ke liye kuch naya sa karate hai.khudako muskurate huye photo me kaid karate hai aur khudako yakin dilate hai.jab usa par jyada like aur views agaye to khudako tassali dilate hai.aur khush rahane ke liye khudahi bahane dhundkar khudako khush mahsus karte hai. Kyun karate hai ye sab ....... Bas ham khush hai is ke liye kuch aur karane ki kya jaroorat hai.kyun hamare khushiyonke mayane badal gaye hai.kyun kuch bhi karane ki aur kisi ko bhi ham khush hai ye prove karane ki jarurat hai ham actual me khush hone ke bad.ham khudake liye khushi dhundate hai ?ya auronke liye?to phir khudake liye khudako khush rakho ham khush hai jo chahiye wo paliya hai ya pana hai bas khush hai thodasa jiliya aur thodasa jina hai. Ham jo hai usame khush hai aur jo bhi chahiye wo milgaya to bhi ham khush hi rahenge.to phir bas accept karo ke aap khush ho aur ab tum jo bhi karoge sahi ke liye karoge soch kar relax karo kyunki badlav aap ke liye sirf aap hi la sakate ho. Kya jarurat hai khush hai isliye kuch bhi dikhava karane ki. Khush hai kisiko bhi samjhane ki. Kuch karana hi chahiye aisi koi bat nahi. Khushi andara se honi chahiye Jo ankhonse chhalakni chahiye aur jo juban se nahi dil se bayan honi chahiye.﻿

author: swati lakwale
text: Happiness ke liye jab tak ham jiyenge ham life ko ji nahi payenge,kyunki life hamare soch aur samaj se bhahut badi hai agar hame khud par aur bhagvan par bharosa hai to jitana ham manga ke nahi pa sakate usse jyada milega......ek hi chees karana hai bas happiness ke liye nahi balki satisfaction ke liye jina kyunki mujhe lagata hai happiness is selfish but satisfaction is selfishness. Kyunki bahot bar aisi situations ajati hai janha hame hamari khushi aur hamari karibiyonki khushi me se ek ko chunana padata hai aur ham hamari chun lete hai par jaisi ki pain aur pleasure dono hi temporary hai to ham thodese time ke liye khush hote to jarur hai par satisfied nahi hote kyunki ek selfish bane wo guilt hame satane lagata hai.is liye hame life me khudake happiness ke beyond jake ham jab sahi waqt par chote chote sahi decision lete hai fair banakar tab hame internally happiness milati hai jab ham sahi soch kar sahi kuch bhi karate hai na to dusare log kya samajhenge kya kahenge isse kuch fark nahi padata kyunki us samay lgata hai maine wohi kiya jitana sahi aur best mai kar sakata tha.aur us samay tumko pata hota hai jo bhi decision maine liya usse mujhe chahe pain mile ya pleasure kya farq padata hai maine jo kiya wo sahi tha.ye sochkar aap andar se satisfied feel karate ho aur agar dard mila bhi to haskar sahalete ho kyunki at that moment aap khush to nahi par sahi jaroor hote ho.to dosto apako happiness nahi bhi milegi phir bhi sukoon rahega.aap satisfied rahoge aur Jindagi me sukh,dukh chalata rahega par jindagi ko khudake liye sachhai se jina aur sukh ke liye nahi balki sahi ke liye jina jyada jaruri hai.to dosto aap hi batao aap selfless happiness ke liye jina chahate ho ya sirf temporary happiness ke liye? Responsible banana aur responsibility ke liye jina. khudake sath auronke liye bhi jina jindagi hai.bas khudako bada banana hai to apane karibiyonke age jo apako matter karate hai unse khudako, apane ego ko thodasa jhukalo.aur dekho unko jitane dene me aur unse argument me harane me bhi ek alaga si khushi milegi.bas dosto jab aap sahi honge apake tarikese to bhagavan apake sath rahenge to kya dar har bat khushi se beyond hogi. Kya sochana aur kyun sochana jindagi wahi sikayegi jo wo chahati ho.so you are already happy just accept it.﻿

author: Aniket Gupta
text: Thanks for your suggestion di but i also wanna share with you that what i sometimes feel is what i am doing is wrong and even my parents do not want me to choose sports as my career. Thus i get confused ki mujhe kya krna chahiye and i should think of it as soon as possible. What i need is just a confirmation or feel comfortable on my decision﻿

author: samarth srivastav
text: Aniket Gupta try to get a clear picture of what you really like doing. For example, I like creating illustrations. Once you are clear with that, research on the net about various careers related to that thing which you like. Believe me you'll find number of good careers in the field. Then find appropriate courses for it. And before jumping into the course try to brush up your skills by watching tutorials on YouTube or any other resource and do it practically. By doing this you'll feel more confident about your abilities and you'll get more determined on getting what you want. While coming back to your studies, choosing a stream for 11th would be secondary! Just choose a stream which has maximum subjects of your interest. For example, if you like stats and economics choose commerce, if you like science choose science, don't think about what you want to become from now. Because there are really number of ways to earn money. Even i was confused when i chose engineering, it was only in my second year when i was exposed to careers in digital artistry , that i chose to be one! And i love doing it irrespective of the money i earn( but just for your information this field does have quite a lot of money ;) but takes a lot of efforts too)!﻿

author: samarth srivastav
text: Aniket Gupta if you want to be a cricketer try to know your skill set better first. Try to see how good you are in cricket as of now, amd try to brush it up by practicing daily , keeping in mind that you take out time for studies as well. It's all about time management. And once you are clear with your motive then with a serious look on the face, just tell your parents what you want to do! Make them understand your passion!(that is only if you really are that passionate about it;) )﻿

author: Aniket Gupta
text: Thank you so much for your suggestions and advise i appreciate it and will definitely think upon it but i would also like to share that there were many instances in my life where i got the opportunity to show that even i can achieve something, can do something in my life if i take sports as my career but i never got a chance to highlight myself. Moreover, if i talk about time management, that along with sports i should give my time to studies, then i think i must give time to any one of the two choices( either to cricket or to my studies) so that i can perfect myself in that perticular choice. So what do u say? What i should i do thn?﻿

author: S Shadow
text: Did anyone told you that School was literally USELESS? Team fearless, I know that we have to live our life, I know that we have to truely live every second. But, school is just here to waste your time, You can't get out because you have homeworks, you have to waste a whole year because you have official exams to pass, you have to waste 7 hours a day learning things that will NEVER help you in this life! b^2-4ac, IN WHAT THIS FORMULA HERE WILL HELP ME IN MY FUTURE?! How can I live life if Parents won't let you get out of house because "you have to study". I'VE SPENT 16 YEARS TO SCHOOL AND WHAT DID I HAVE?! What? Answer this question here, what did I have..? A diploma? A diploma.. Heh.. This is laughable, tell me why most of the successful people YOU HAVE MENTIONNED in this video, are dropouts, why only dropouts are successful, oh wait a second, because they knew that they had to get out of that road, what kind of road? That road where everyone is walking on, EVERYONE!!! We are living a LIE god damn it!!! That road tells us to: Go to school, go to the university, find a job that you DO NOT like just for MONEY and WORK FOR SOMEBODY (you'll be an employee in most of the cases), have a familly, and die. Is that life? Is that life?! NO AND NO this is a life of someone who is living a LIE, for the familly, in most of the cases, THERE IS PROBLEMS, THERE IS PROBLEMS, why only few people are living happily with their familly and the rest are having problems? Why..? Because they do not understand? No, because they haven't be taught how to be happy, they haven't be taught how to choose your partner, they haven't been taught all of this.. What they have been taught you say? They have been taught how to do maths, they have been taught that "having problems in a relation ship is normal", they have been taught to do anything for money, and not for themselves, they have been taught BULLSHIT! I have a goal in life, but too bad I have to wait until I pass those exams I have, to be free. That goal, is to awake people, to tell them that they are living a lie, that they have to be themselves but not to be who they think they are, I have to tell them that if they truely love themselves, they would work on themselves: If you were obese, you would work on yourself because you truely love yourself and you don't want to die because of obesity (that's an example), if you want to have Randy Orton's body, you would WORK to have it, you would GO to the gym! I personally do go to the gym, it's been 3 weeks now, thank god my parents agreed and didn't told me to stay at home because I have exams to pass or homeworks to do. Now, how would I make this happen? How can I achieve my goal? I have a plan, I already have a plan, guys, I'm 17 years old and I clearly know what to do in life, and how to do it, I want to be a movie producer and make movies about those lies we're living I want to make interviews, I want to talk about that on TV, on the media, SHARE IT EVERYWHERE!!! I do make montage, I do graphic designs on Blender, I want to share it at any cost. As for love, I'm not going to search for it, no. I'm instead going to wait, until I find that this person fits with me, love isn't only by "seeing" someone, or "looking" at someone, love comes after friendship, you have to live things with that friend, you have to know how this person thinks, now, of course, not everyone can have the same thought, if you were about to argue to see who the heck is right about something, it means that you don't love the person that is right in front of you, because, who cares about who is right or who is wrong? Now there's limits, of course (am I getting off topic lmao?) if you love someone that says: killing is good, you should do something, of course (I'll just ask how you could love someone that loves killing lol, but idc love is love 😉). Just wanted to point that out.. School is useless, it teaches you: you failed a test, you're a failure. It does not teaches you: You failed a test, you will do better next time. Nah hell no they aren't teaching you that (now there's billions of school out there, and I'm sure there's great ones that has a good system, like FINLAND school system or Khan Akademy). "I'll not say that life isn't fair, because we haven't truely living it yet"- S Shadow. There, I made a quote. :)﻿

text: When does it become burning yourself out, because you studied so hard and the expectations for yourself become so high? When does it become when studying for tests and quizzes become an obsession? When does not having friends or a social do to the mind when you isolate yourself and live into the depression of loneliness and sadness? author: Marisol Zeledón
text: wow, don't you just LOVE when someone encases people in a category? It's like they think they know more about you than yourself. Let's debunk every part of this incredibly ignorant comment so this self-entitled person actually tries and inform themselves (maybe YOU need to spend a little more time on the internet doing some actual reading), hold on tight cause it's a long one: 1. Millennails are lazt af. Oh really, funny how millennials show A LOT HIGHER graduation rates from high school, and even more college enrollment than non-millennial generations. I don't know what your definition of lazy is, but in my world working hard to be a professional in something is the opposite of being lazy. Sorry we aren't a bunch of dropouts who decided living a mediocre life was enough (yeah I'm talking to you "millennials lack purpose" guy). I'm just shoving these facts here since you didn't really say why are we lazy exactly. Is it cause we spend time on the internet? honey, we were born in a technological era, thanks to technology we actually do have more dreams and high goals, besides, didn't yall spend all your time listening to the radio or watching tv all day? 2. That last point in 1 actually brings me to this one, what exactly do you call being in "reality" lmfao. Last time I checked we millennials have to deal with the fucking mess your generations made. It so much more expensive to live, to buy a house, to be economically stable.. etc. We spend time on the internet because times have evolved, should we just sit on our asses all day playing yaxes then? And actually, news and information are SO accessible and fast-traveling thanks to the internet, we GET a picture of reality, trust me, we just don't have to wait a week till it's printed on a newspaper. We end up making wrong decisions? is that a millennial thing really? here was I thinking that that's how a human learns and gains experience. (btw didn't your generations feel the need to spend millions on armies and guns instead of focusing on education, health and stability?) 3. "Knowing reality" is something a human being in this society learns from experience, times have changed and yeah we didn't grow up like you did, that doesn't mean we lack sensibility, actually, I think millennials are the most hopeful, humanitarian and socially aware generation thanks to the atrocities your generation did, thank you for showing us how it ISN'T done. The struggles we encounter as adults are not because we're lazy, it's cause of the world that was inherited to us and the systems that were taught to us that are obsolete and failed to adapt to a fast developing society, the education system is a perfect example, are you really blaming us for being shoved into these systems that don't fit us anymore? They say that knowledge is freedom, the more you learn, the better version of yourself you are, so yes, it is about books and not just books, but videos, blogs, articles, etc that are available to us with a click. P.S I'm aware past generations did inherit us all these tools we can develop ourselves with, I'm just stating that ya'll created these tools and for some reason don't expect us to use them or adapt to them. We millennials are hopeful and full of creativity, you know what really gets in our way? idiots encasing us in a box with set characteristics because they are too narrow minded to actually inform themselves, you know, like the ones who think they know about you more than you know about yourself.﻿

author: Ethan Hamilton
text: As much as I agree with this video's motives, sometimes you need to relax, you NEED to "waste" time or you will burn out. You say that you need to do things you enjoy, but imply that playing video games or spending time with friends is a waste? Surely if you enjoy something, you are filling your life with more happy memories. If your goal is only to work more, then will you ever reach your goal? Surely a life spent with no relaxation or time just to breathe is more of a waste than one with less stress and happiness. Yes you need to work hard, but you need to play hard too, this balance is importance. It seems as if work or leisure are two separate things, but can't we have both? Although you say each second you "waste" could be used to gain knowledge to make you more successful, you could have also spent those few seconds appreciating the world around you, the people around you, the family around you. After all, a clear mind has more room to understand new things than one already crumbling under stress. No matter how knowledgable or "successful" you are, in the end we are all people and once our lives are over, they are equally over. I for one fall as a victim to over stress about work and have lost many opportunities in life because of it. Yes, without work we do not get rewards, but we need to spend time appreciating the rewards life has giving us too.﻿

author: SvenSekulic
text: Some of the things they said are true. But the fact that they think playing video games and partying is bad and reading books is good suprises me. This is a motivational video, not "Every parent ever". I mean I get it that most of the people use video games as a drug of some kind and yes those people need to get their shit together and start being productive but there are some people that are happy with their life spent on video games and in clubs. If you tell them that the only way of spending time usefully is by reading books, then they will believe that they are usefull only when they read and some day they are gonna realise that they never accomplished their dreams, instead they spent their life doing "the right thing". What I suggest and personally do is: every day spend an hour or so doing what you really want to. The rest of the day you can do what society wants you too (read books, study, be smart, be productive and all that shit). And I suggest you to get your shit together because if you really need a motivational video to encourage you to kick ass then you are not believing in yourself.﻿

author: Gaurav Gautam
text: Okay, so is becoming the best version of yourself means being famous, being rich, and being successful? Is this what this video is giving the message? Is this what the real definition of being the "Best Version Of Yourself" is meaning having to accomplish all of these things in life? Because somehow I find this video a little contradicted? I mean, I truly understand the whole "never stop learning part in life" and "reading books" and "never give up to chase your dreams" but the moment he says that the "The success is not about the money, the fame or the big house. It's in fact about becoming the "Best Version of Yourself... now, you see this is the part where I get distracted the most when the speaker emphasizes so much on being "The Richest Man" and "how the Richest Man Bill Gates was once asked a question and The Richest Man Replied and many more times... repeating the same thing and yet trying to give the message that to be the "Best Verison of Yourself."... is not about any of these things? I mean... Well, my only question is that can one not become the best version of himself without being rich, famous, and successful, unlike Bill, Warren, and Opera, they are all rich? No wonder that they are all nice people but I DO know for sure that they are so many richest people on this planet and they are definitely NOT the best version kind of people... I truly find that the title of this video should not be what it is...just wanted to say what I felt that's all... To me, what I believe that becoming the "Best Version of Yourself" is entirely a whole different thing...It's all about who and what you are from the INSIDE, and not the OUTSIDE and certainly not having all the money in the world...﻿

author: meropale
text: Definitely *FITNESS*, specifically running. Running is my "keystone" habit. I also read and meditate but running is the one habit that makes all the difference and makes everything else that I do less of a burden. If I only read or only meditate I just don't get the same benefits, but if I run then this permeates in very positive ways through the rest of my life. The result is that meditation and reading seem easier and more natural to do. For me meditation/reading do not make me more motivated to run. In any case I am not knocking meditation or reading. Added in with the running meditation and reading definitely make me much more emotionally strong. There have been a couple of times where I have injured myself as a runner so I have to be careful in the future to maintain strength and flexibility. In the past I've only focused on running but this time around I'm including the strength training and stretching to support the running. It will become even more important as I get older. This is not a 21 day habit, nor something I would just do for a year and then just stop. It really is a habit that needs to be maintained throughout your life. It sounds painful and overwhelming in the beginning to think that far ahead since we are so used to getting our fix without having to wait but over time you complain less and less about it and really start to see how your whole mindset shifts and you realize the putting in the effort is very much worth it. You do get the feeling that brighter days are ahead and that even if dark days do come you'll have the strength to deal with them.﻿

author: Colette N.
text: I’ve actually recently started meditating. I’d tried it a few times, but I just couldn’t get into it. I think the reason I had more success with it in these last couple of weeks is because I realized one of the causes of my depression is running away from my problems via distraction. I couldn’t remember the last time I just sat down without doing anything but relaxing. I’m always staring at my phone and watching videos, posting on Facebook, just a bunch of stuff. What I do, for those of you trying to start meditation, is I put some relaxing music on and set a timer on my phone. Start out with less time, probably ten minutes or so, and just sit with your eyes closed and relax. DO NOT CHECK THE TIMER!! You know how long you set it for, don’t worry about how much time is left. I just did my first 30 minute meditation, and it helps so much. I think within the next week, I’d like to try to take up reading a book.﻿

author: Meow
text: I'll tell you a trick. Start with reading. If you started reading, read on fitness/diets/nutrition or meditation/yoga (Whispers: Yoga is 2 in 1). Once you pick up the habit, you will now have some knowledge or motivation to meditate or exercise. Starting the next one would be easy. You'll be picking 2 habits at once. One result that's likely to happen is you finish reading to apply. HENCE, doing two of these habits at once ;) Another thing that would make your life great is waking up 2 hours earlier. In these 2 hours you can do all of the 3 habits. Say you'd read 25 pages, meditate for 15 min and exercise for 20 min with 10 warm up. You will feel productive and great to have a great start of the day ;) Waking up early is the mother habits, if you mastered it your life will tremendously change. But for starter, try the first trick for a week or two, then try waking up early to read alone. Once you pick up reading, add meditation and fitness to the early routine. Trust me, your life will change. Be smart ;)﻿

author: AntonioKowatsch
text: Hokum... I can read an entire book in one sitting and I never get angry (because I have my emotions completely under control thanks to my understanding of stoicism). I didn't achieve this focus because of meditation but rather because of my calling. I realized what my ideal self would look like and started to aspire to it. I've read well over a thousand books by now (which is not that impressive once you realize that I read about 100 books each year) and if there's one thing that I can tell you it's that philosophical literature has had the biggest impact on my world view. Those are the real gems.... things that can't just be taught in courses. People have to actually develop themselves to the point where they are willing to do work in order to obtain knowledge. Watching a video is the easiest thing in the world. It's akin to junk food. Reading a book on the other hand is an ergodic activity. One has to wrap his mind around concepts and create mental images of their own instead of watching another persons animations. But then again.... most of you people will never understand what I'm trying to convey here. You're not ready yet.﻿

author: Ken W
text: Leasing a car is a bad idea for many reasons. The first reason is at the end of the lease you have nothing to show for all the money that you spent. You either must turn the car into the dealer (where they try to convince you to trade up to a new lease) or you must purchase the car at the end of the lease. There are also hidden fees associated with leasing a car. Often the mileage limits are difficult to stay under, and you may find yourself paying over mileage charges at the end of your lease. Leasing is similar to renting a home, you are constantly paying money and in the end you have nothing to show for it.﻿

author: Natemesis
text: @christopher, others, You sound foolish saying leasing is a foolish idea. Did you work the math out or just guessing? If you normally buy a brand new car, then leasing makes more sense. The lower monthly lease payment compared to a loan payment saves more money than buying new, paying it off, selling and buying new again. You also don't have to worry about repairs. Buying used is often less expensive than both options assuming you can maintain a car. If you buy new and keep forever then you could save money buying used then keeping forever. Maybe you prefer being the only owner and can't maintain the car. Maybe you should look at leasing. It depends on your car buying/maintaining habits. Queue request @improvement pill for best car habits.﻿

author: Damian Rivas
text: There's actually huge benefits to leasing a car, and renting a home/apartment. Not everyone has the same needs and habits as you do. Leasing a car works perfectly for those who want, and can afford, to drive the newest cars. See, for me leasing a car would be perfect if I didn't like to drive long distances multiple times a year. If all I did was commute to work day in and day out, then there would be no reason not to lease a car. Also, owning a home is a stupid idea FOR ME because it goes against my current goal of living free and not being tied down to anything. At least, not yet. When I'm older and ready to settle down, I will definitely buy a home to live in. For now, the only properties I'll be buying are ones I intend to rent out.﻿

author: Andy Dietrich
text: Ken W I seriously can't believe he used "lease a car instead of buying" as a foundation of learning money management. When you buy a car, ITS YOURS. THAT IS YOUR LEGAL PROPERTY. A lease is essentially renting a car for two years with extreme restrictions. That, combined with the offhand comment that history is useless in every day life (when it has literally shaped our present and will continue to shape our future, and presents outliers for what's to come) makes me question the rest of this advice. This all just seems very elementary and poorly presented.﻿

author: Yann Larriau
text: Andy Dietrich the comments about school not being useful are indeed the worst part of the video: clearly most people in this thread would benefit from a couple more calculus lessons to understand why leasing a car can be (and often is) better than buying it. What is the financial value of something being "your own legal property"? Zero. You have to look at this from a financial point of view. Leasing a car is usually less expensive than buying new then reselling every x years. Just like renting a place to live can be more financially beneficial than buying one.﻿

author: TDFXX
text: Ken W You can adjust as the mileage limit at the end of the lease. I don‘t understand why they allow that, but I had such a situation a few weeks ago. Also, you can lease a car for 3 years, return it and lease the next car, a newer model for 3 years. I prefer having the newest model over an old, ugly pile of junk any day of the week. I think there is hardly anyone who doesn‘t want another car or the newer model of his current car after 3-4 years of owning it.﻿

author: Andy Dietrich
text: Yann Larriau First of all, calculus has nothing to do with finances, solvency, and the accompanying break even analysis one would conduct to decide if leasing or purchasing would be better for a particular situation - so your false equivalency already gives me a negative impression of your critical thinking skills. Owning a car, and having it as "legal property" means you control the title, and once it's paid off it's paid off. It's capital. The second you lease a car, all it's doing is depreciating. I personally don't know anyone that does or would "buy a car every few years". I have a car from 1981 that is perfectly operational - so that's a moot point. Owning a car gives you capital whereas continuously leasing is just a liability. If your cash flow changes due to extraneous situations, that lease will be a further burden just for having means of transposition. I made my first six figures at 24 but what do I know.﻿

author: Warren Van Niekerk
text: Spot on with Meditation!!!! Learning about Vipassana taught me the true use of meditation. Been "reading", watching videos and learning about meditation for years, then occasionally do a 5min to 10min actual sit down....... .....but after doing it daily (20mins thrice per day), wow, what a change in 1 single week of doing this compared to years of intellectually understanding it. It's funny how it's become my "go to" thing when I feel down. I no longer crave to change the external situation to feel better, I go sit for a while (20mins) in my angry or anxious state, get into that space, start feeling great, then go change the external event with a positive outlook. It is so difficult to make it a daily practice as it feels like you wasting time that could be used to change your situation, but once you into it you will understand - it kinda feels like you have more time and don't have that rush mentality and things still get done on time and in better spirits.﻿

author: Lu Peters
text: Your example shows the biggest missing piece in your argument: mimetic desire. The reason the person quit smoking was not self motivation, but external motivation. The most important habit is surrounding myself with people who already do what I want to be doing. Because humans are mimetic creatures / social learners we copy the habits of our surroundings. This makes it much easier to adopt new or change old habits. It's why your example suddenly was into fitness and diet, it's also why fat people have fat friends. Reading works exactly that way. It exposes me / my brain to behaviors that can be mimicked. Same goes for video by the way. I can also listen to podcasts. As long as I am paying attention the medium doesn't matter too much. Fitness is the same thing. Nobody eats healthy because they do fitness. They eat healthy because other people, who do fitness, eat healthy.﻿

author: klokmedia
text: Tayshaun Haynes hey man don’t complicate it by worrying about what is the best time, or even what is the best exercise. Just get the habit of being active started, you can refine it later. It is much easier to keep a habit if it’s at the same time each day because the time of day acts as a reminder or trigger. But you might be able to use something else as a reminder. For me I have only one rule for fitness - I must put my running shoes on after work. That’s it! It’s a stupidly simple goal but it works like this - If I don’t feel active after work I will put my shoes on and then feel like I have completed my goal. I allow myself to not feel bad if I don’t go work out. That’s very important. Here’s the secret though. Nearly every time I put my shoes on, even if I feel terrible, I’ll walk down to the park anyway. Then nearly every time I’ll go for a run or do a calisthenics work out. I’m pretty much tricking myself into working out and doing something. Even a short half arsed workout is better than not leaving the house. I’ve been doing this for a couple of years now and I have easily made it into a habit that I enjoy. I look and feel great and I’ve found activities that I love and fit well into my lifestyle. Just get moving man, anytime of day :)﻿

author: mecanicien37
text: Haces lo siguiente: Cuando termines tu rutina de ejercicios. Entonces vas a casa o si puedes en tu gimnasio o no se , en el parque puede ser si lo haces al aire libre. Entonces en ese estado donde el cuerpo necesita estar relajado y descansar. Aprovechas a sentarte un momento a solas, un lugar donde no te molesten por al menos unos 10 minutos y te sientas comodamente pero con Atencion y Alerta, sin DORMIRTE, pues no se trata de dormirse. Una vez elijas el lugar y el momento, simplemente te sientas comodamente solo, sin distracciones de ningun tipo, de preferencia cierras los ojos y lo mas probable es que empezara a sonar la famosa "vocecita" en tu cabeza que te empezara a "hablar" de todo (Pasado ,presente y futuro)lo que no has hecho, etc. Entonces esos pensamientos que surgen, tu los ves , sin criticarlos, sin aferrarte a ellos. Igual como cuando vas al cine y ves una pelicula. Estas sentado viendo un film y solo eres un testigo de lo que acontece en la pantalla. Igual, es lo que pasara cuando estes sentado en silencio y entonces solo permanece como un testigo nada mas. Y asi lo que dure y decidas sentarte. Despues de esto, de ver tu propia pelicula ,sin haberla criticado, sin poner nigun comentario, etc. entonces sigues tu vida normal. Poco a poco si lo practicas, esta interiorizacion te ira dando mas y mas respuestas sobre preguntas que siempre has tenido. Los libros, pues lee los temas que te atraigan. Dedica un dia a visitar una buena libreria y dedica un tiempo adecuado sin prisa y tension a ver las estanterias y te puedo asegurar que al leer algunos, encontraras el adecuado, y esto sucede asi porque de manera muy extraña, suele ser "El libro quien llama al lector".﻿

author: Sherri James
text: I agree with each of these habits and incorporate all 3. I would like to offer an alternative look at grade school. Any system can be improved; and the system through which we educate our students can be improved. At the same time, the things we learn in school provide a basic foundation upon which all the other knowledge we acquire later in life is built. The lessons we learn later in life needs something to stand on when it enters our brains and that "formal" education provides that. Perhaps we should not sell students on the idea that their education is complete once they finish school. There's no way any of us can know with absolute certainty all that we'll need to know later in life. If there was a tweak I'd make to the education system, it would be placing an emphasis on how to learn. In this way, when students leave the "formal" education system, they have an understanding that they are now taking over the responsibility of educating themselves because there's no way that any school system could ever teach all that needs to be known. Students need to really grasp that what they're receiving is a foundation that will assist in the assimilation of everything else they'll learn over their lifetime.﻿

author: Academic Excellence 📚💡📝
text: Some guy I read one novel per week and workout 3-4 times per week, lifting and cardio. I also meditate every other day for at least 15 min. While all these habits may be conducive to a healthy, happy, lifestyle, there is one particular weakness that will throw all of these off. That weakness is poor sleep. If your not receiving the proper sleep your body needs daily, then you can train your brain (so to speak) all you want, but will continue to fall short of your goals until you give your body adequate rest. Not a professional health specialist, but personally this seems to be the key for my lifestyle.﻿

author: Lua Veli
text: Hi Jason. Great question! I wanted to recommend you three books I loved: 1. "Amador" by the spanish philosopher Fernando Savater. He wrote it for his 15 year old son. 2. "Wide Awake : A Budhist Guide for Teens" by Diana Winston. She is a wonderful meditation teacher. I once watched a lesson on meditation from Yale University on youtube and the professor recommended her guided meditation podcasts. To find them just search for: "UCLA Hammer Meditation" on Itunes. 3. Let me tell you a story by Jorge Bucay. He is a very beloved Argenitinian psychologist. In the book he has this teenaged patient and for every problem he tells during the sessions, Jorge Bucay tells him a very interesting story , related to that problem. That's the kind of book you would finish in one day and never forget! Best wishes :- )﻿

To find it just search for this on youtube: " Human Emotions II, Mindfulness, Yale University" The professor there recommends the guided meditation podcasts by Diana Winston. I am using them since 5 years. They are excellent. To find them just search for: " UCLA Hammer Meditation" on Itunes. Doing it with a meditation teacher feels much better and you stop doubting whether you are doing it right or not. Just try the podcast. Many greetings and best wishes :- )﻿

text: I'm going to choose meditation as my keystone habit for the rest of the course. It's something I've been working on for the past three weeks, so I want to keep it going. I'm noticing significant changes within my life, including all of the aforementioned in the video. My reason for choosing meditation as my keystone habit is because I know that our thoughts create our reality. When I am in the process of changing my relationship with my thoughts, I change my relationship with reality. I can navigate thoughts with more awareness, clarity and understanding as I journey through meditation. Once I reach automaticity with meditation, my mind will be sharpened and focused which will allow other tasks and habits to be dealt with relative ease. Thanks for these videos and I'll be supporting on Patreon!﻿

author: James
text: I know English is the number 1 universal language in the world & I'm British BUT English isn't my real native language/first language. I was born in England but moved to France when I was 3, so I didn't attend any schools, colleges or uni in England therefore it's impossible to learn all the English words by attending nursery! . Also I spent most of my time sleeping & not listening to the teacher when I was at school 😄. So that explains why I'm not fluent in English, It also explains why I make spelling mistakes when I write in English ( for example how can you tell the difference between then & than? Or whether embarrassing is spelt "embarassing" or "embarrasing" It's basic mistakes like that that can't be solved by watching tv series,films) My grammar/vocabulary is not 100% correct how could it be if I left England when I was 3? Also I didn't attend primary school, nor did I attend any high school, college, 6th form, grammar secondary school so that explains why I'm worse at writing in English than speaking it. And why I make mistakes in grammer/vocabulary 😊 As for speaking English, it's normal I'm not 100% fluent, there are a few words that I stilll don't know, especially some English dialects such as some scouse or cockney expressions/slang words, how am I supposed to know them if I grew up in France? Not to mention the English classes I had at school/college in France were just basic English ( no wonder the French/Italians suck at speaking English 😂) & back then from 2000-2007 the English taught at school was very basic compared to nowadays. Also I didn't take any English classes outside of school so all the English I've learnt is from watching TV & listening to music!﻿

author: W E
text: I think that reading English books can help you improve your writing, reading, and speaking skills but it has nothing to do with improving your pronunciation. In my opinion, the best way of speaking English with a good accent is to listen to English native speakers. You can also refer to some well-known English dictionaries such as Merriam-Webster, Oxford, Cambridge, and Longman. They can help you distinguish sounds with the assistance of the phonetics included in them.﻿

author: J. W. K.
text: The narrator is fluent, his pronunciation is clear. He does not quite sound native. However, always remember: you may learn stategies for increasing your proficiency from a non-native, strategies that a native speaker may never have thought of! Therefore, do not discount the ideas of an extremely proficient non-native. Also, practice in Front of a mirror can help: you can overcome shyness, observe your facial expressions, Position of the mouth in forming words, etc. By the way, the suggestions in this video really work: I did it with German and French as I was learning, before anyone made a video or even suggested this method! I am glad someone cared to put these suggestions out on YouTube. Well done!!!﻿

author: J. W. K.
text: It is Not a question of accent. He speaks English fluently, without hesitation. His grammar is excellent, and his pronunciation is clear enough. The former Secretary of State in the UDA, Dr. Henry Kissinger, has a rather head accent, comparitively speaking. I as a native süesker, would not hesitated to ask him a question about proper usage of any word or expression. Dou completely missed the point of this presentation, and that is indeed unfortunate. Watch again, this time without any prejudice or preconceived notions: it is a Strategy that works for bin native speakers to learn to speak without hesitating as much. He did not make any Promise about a perfect accent, and fluency does not mean a perfect accent, rather merely that one can be easily understood and can speak in a flowing, connected Männer. Have a nice day.﻿

author: soultrail7
text: If you don't have anybody to speak with, well even if you have such person, I'd strongly recommend to record yourself while speaking or retelling stuff. Then listen to yourself and you will finally be able to see the most persistent mistakes in grammar, intonation and lexicon and to be mindful of them during the next speaking session. It's like becoming your own tutor. However unpleasant for some the experience of listening their own voice may be, it has proven to be the most effective tactics for many people.﻿

author: zack khai
text: Apart from reading and watching english materials, I would say that listening to english songs and singing to them helped me a lot when I was young. Music helps with the correct pronunciation, varying my tones and rhythm while at the same time practicing my breathing to be more relaxed. The effect of music to your mood also adds to the fun way of improving my english. If I wanted more challenge, I'd pick up a fast-tempo songs, borderline rap, or just try to pick up the song lyrics that I've never heard before and memorizing them soon after. With english, its not the speed of your speech that's important in communication, rather its how well one is able to converse as natural and casual so that the other person may understood you better. Furthermore, if you're able to speak in a more relaxed tempo and manner, you're able to sync your thoughts at the same pace as your speech is.﻿

author: Rogers Steve
text: Chen Kevin.. Hi there man!! I think that writing down all the things you hear it's going to help you in grammar, more than speaking. I believe that if you want to become more fluent orally you have to listen to the language and then produce sentences, could be the same sentences you heard or new ones. To write better you have to read more and then write down things, but to speak better you have to listen and speak more and more without "thinking" just let the language become part of you and get immersed/submerged in it.. I hope this was helpful to you, regards!!﻿

author: EngFluent
text: So your problem is that you know the words but you often don't know how to pronounce them, and that causes you to hesitate when talking, right? The best way to solve this problem (in my view) is basic imitation (link below): English Speaking Practice (very easy to do) After doing the exercise consistently for a while, your brain will learn how to convert words into the right sequence of mouth movements. And that's how you improve :)﻿
